    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:help!` doesn't show easter egg `E478: Don't panic!`, but instead it points to help file for `!` command.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\n`:help!`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:help!` should print `E478: Don't panic!`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n---\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian 13\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
